# Licensing (English)

This repository contains two categories of content with different licenses:

1. Documentation (all files under `docs/` unless otherwise noted) is licensed under Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC BY 4.0).
2. Example scripts / configuration snippets (if added) are licensed under the GNU General Public License v3.0 or later (GPL-3.0-or-later) unless a file header states otherwise.

Open Journal Systems (OJS) is © Public Knowledge Project (PKP) and distributed under GNU GPL v3. See: https://pkp.sfu.ca/ojs/

## Attribution Requirements
- Credit: "Public Knowledge Project (PKP)".
- Link to https://pkp.sfu.ca/ and the OJS project page.
- Retain original GPL and CC BY notices in redistributed or derivative works.

## CC BY 4.0 (Summary)
Official: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/
You are free to Share and Adapt with Attribution and without adding further restrictions.

## GPL v3 (Summary)
Official: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.txt
Copyleft license permitting commercial use, modification, distribution, patent use, private use; requires source disclosure and same license.

SPDX-License-Identifier: CC-BY-4.0 AND GPL-3.0-or-later

